atom.val: An opaque (low-level) hash operation used to implement hashing for pointers. -/

The `BEq ` and `Hashable ` instances on `` are compatible. This means that that `a == b` implies
`hash a = hash b`.

This is automatic if the `BEq` instance is lawful.
-/
If `a == b`, then `hash a = hash b`. -/

A lawful hash function respects its Boolean equality test.
